Qing Wu

Feel free to find me in any way you like :)

I am Qing Wu (吴晴 in Chinese), a final-year Ph.D. student in SMILE LAB at ShanghaiTech University, advised by Prof. Yuyao Zhang. Before that, I received my B.E. degree at China University of Geosciences, Wuhan in 2020.

I am interested in varying topics related to inverse imaging problems. Currently, my research is focused on:

  • CT/MRI Undersampled Reconstruction
  • MRI Motion Correction
  • CT Acqusition Self-Calaribation
  • Quantitative CT (e.g., Material Decomposition)

See more in the detailed CV.
